<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Flowering from May to August, fruiting from July to September.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
The specific epithet refers to the short cylinder perianth limb of the new species. The 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“brevi”">&quot;brevi&quot;</normalizedToken>
means 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“short”">&quot;short&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“limbum”">&quot;limbum&quot;</normalizedToken>
means 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“limb”">&quot;limb&quot;</normalizedToken>
, so the new species is named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="X. X. Zhu, Jun Wang &amp; F. Cao" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Isotrema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Isotrema brevilimbum" order="Piperales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevilimbum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Isotrema brevilimbum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
