<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="preliminary conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Preliminary conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName authorityName="X. X. Zhu, Jun Wang &amp; F. Cao" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Isotrema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Isotrema brevilimbum" order="Piperales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevilimbum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Isotrema brevilimbum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from a single population including two individuals on the roadside of farmland. The new species is assigned a preliminary status of vulnerable (VU) according to the IUCN Red List Categories (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B19" refString="IUCN, 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, Version 3.1 (2nd Ed.) Gland and Cambridge, 32 pp." title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, Version 3.1 (2 nd Ed.) Gland and Cambridge, 32 pp." year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
). However, since very few details exist about its natural distribution, the lack of sufficient data currently does not allow a final risk evaluation and the species might be regarded as data deficient (DD). Further field surveys in western Guizhou and northeastern Yunnan are needed to gain more information on its distribution. Not only is the area not under protection as a nature reserve, but also habitat disturbance brought about by human activities, such as grazing and farming, may have a negative impact on the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aristolochiaceae" genus="Isotrema" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Isotrema wardianum" order="Piperales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wardianum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Isotrema wardianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously only known from Myanmar and India. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sun, H" journalOrPublisher="Yunnan Science &amp; Technology Press, Kunming" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B27" refString="Sun, H, Zhou, ZK, 2002. Seed Plants of The Big Bend Gorge of Yalu Tsangpo in SE Tibet, E Himalayas. Yunnan Science &amp; Technology Press, Kunming" title="Seed Plants of The Big Bend Gorge of Yalu Tsangpo in SE Tibet, E Himalayas." year="2002">Sun and Zhou (2002)</bibRefCitation>
later reported the species from China, according to a specimen collected from Medog County of Tibet (
